<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1905-07-01T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1905-07-01T00:00:00-05:00" n="893" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d893">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">President <persName type="from">Roosevelt</persName>
                                to Ambassador <persName type="to">Meyer</persName>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">The
                                        White House</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1905-07-01"><hi rend="italic">July 1,
                                1905</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>On Monday I shall announce the appointment of plenipotentiaries by name,
                            stating that they will be clothed with full powers to negotiate and
                            conclude treaty of peace subject to ratification by home governments. *
                            * *</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Theodore
                            Roosevelt.</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>